  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> waxy potatoes</strong> in half and add to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Once fork-tender, add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and gently mix together – these are your <strong>buttery potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and roughly chop</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into bite-sized pieces – this is your <strong>smashed cucumber</strong></p><p>Tip: Bash the cucumber in its bag to avoid mess. By bruising the cucumber, the water is drawn out more easily!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> halloumi</strong> into thick slices</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced halloumi </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>smashed cucumber</strong> (save the rest for later!) to a bowl with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>mint sauce </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chunky tzatziki</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-halloumi-with-buttery-potatoes-and-chunky-tzatziki/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> halloumi</strong> with the <strong>buttery potatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped lettuce</strong> and <strong>chunky tzatziki</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the lettuce with the<strong> remaining smashed cucumber</strong>, then dress with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Drizzle your<strong> red chilli relish</strong> over the halloumi</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
